build/target-cache/
build/.lln-cache/
**/.lln-cache/
**/*.egraph.json
**/*.egraph.json.gz
.logicn/capabilities.local.json
.logicn/capabilities.local.*
packages-logicn/logicn-core/examples/benchmark-results/*.json
packages-logicn/logicn-devtools-benchmarks/results/history/
/NOTES TO COVER
/notes/*
# ── Secrets / signing material — NEVER commit (CRITICAL, 2026-06-06) ──
.env.logicn-signing
.env.*.signing
**/*.signing
*.private.pem
**/*-private.pem
.env.local
.env.*.local
# Auto-provisioned dev signing pubkeys (zero-touch key lifecycle regenerates these per
# machine alongside the gitignored private key — they are build artifacts, not source).
**/governance/signing-key-*.pub.pem
# ── Build / test scratch (do not commit) ──
test-output.txt
**/*.pdb
build/*.out
build/full-flight-*/

# ── Ephemeral build/compile outputs (regenerated by `logicn build` + tests; never source) ──
build/*.wat
build/*.wasm
build/*.lmanifest
build/*.lmanifest.json
build/*.governance-impact.json
build/*.lln
build/_*.log
build/_*.json
build/*.snap
# Runtime/test scratch (audit ledgers, egress/flight test dirs) — NOT build/graph or build/kb-graph
build/audit-log/
build/egress-it-*/
build/full-flight-*/
build/tower-logs/
build/receipt-ledger/
build/bench-report.md
build/*.dot

# build/graph: ignore the heavy REGENERATED artifacts (2.1 MB json churns every `graph` run;
# the json is rebuilt by `graph` — `graph query/explain/path` print "run graph first" if absent).
# KEEP the small human/AI nav docs (LogicN_GRAPH_REPORT.md, logicn-ai-map.md — AGENTS.md points to them).
build/graph/*.json
build/graph/*.html
build/kb-graph/*.json
build/kb-graph/*.dot
build/graph/*.dot
